\begin_layout Subsubsection
Input
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The therapist selects 
\begin_inset Quotes fld
\end_inset

Guide Blind-Teo Game
\begin_inset Quotes frd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Goal
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The goal of the game is to help the child to associate the sequence presented
 to a spatial relation with the physical checkpoints.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Rules
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The child and Teo share sufficiently large space to move around.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

The game starts with a ’blindfolded’ Teo, which explains the child the dynamic
 of the game.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

In a display it is shown to the kid a sequence of checkpoints that he has
 to help Teo to arrive while Teo’s blindfolded.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

The child must move to the check point and call ’Teo, here!’ so Teo could
 start moving in his direction.
\begin_inset Float figure
placement H
wide false
sideways false
status collapsed

